<HEADLINE>
SPORTS STARS CHEER ON RUNNERS IN TAIPEI'S 'NIKE 5K RUN'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Dec. 7 (CNA) 01/07/07  18:16:01 (By Y.L.Kao)
</P>
<P>
A "Nike 5K Run, " with sports stars cheering on runners along the
way, was held in Taipei Sunday amid cold weather, marking
Taiwan's first road race of the new year.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Nike Group, the event's organizer, said that to
draw the most number of participants Nike had decided on 5km as
the course's length, which is most suitable for all ages.
</P>
<P>
Adding that to boost competitors' morale, the organizer also
invited basketball baseball players Chen Chih-yuan, Chen Kuan-
ren, Yeh Yung-chieh and Peng Cheng- shin to cheer them on at the
midway point.
</P>
<P>
While national basketball players Chien Wei-chuan and Chen Chih-
yuan rode alongside runners in a press vehicle, Ho Sho-cheng,
Tseng Wen-ding and Yueh Ying-li rode bicycles at the end of the
route to spur runners to do their best.
</P>
<P>
Lu Chih-tsung and Lin Nien-tse, both students at the National
College of Pysical Education and Sports in Kueishan, Taoyuan
County, won the race in male and female categories, respectively.
</P>
